 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2776/about-advanced-window-move/?answer=2777#post-id-2777</link><description>You almost answered your own question already:

Focus the left terminal, split it vertically, then move the bottom terminal to the left.</description><pubDate>Thu, 24 Oct 2013 18:33:09 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2776/about-advanced-window-move/?answer=2777#post-id-2777</guid></item><item><title>Comment by Rodrigo Azevedo for &lt;p&gt;You almost answered your own question already:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Focus the left terminal, split it vertically, then move the bottom terminal to the left.&lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2776/about-advanced-window-move/?comment=2781#comment-2781</link><description>Thank you very much Michael! It was more easy than I thought!</description><pubDate>Thu, 24 Oct 2013 18:42:04 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2776/about-advanced-window-move/?comment=2781#comment-2781</guid></item><item><title>Answer by Rodrigo Azevedo for &lt;p&gt;I3 is awesome, but I didn't found a solution for this.&lt;/p&gt;

